<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-808] Segfault when constant declaration references a struct field that doesn&apos;t exist</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-808</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When attempting to generate code for a Thrift file like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
struct X {
  required string my_field;
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; X CONSTANT_X = {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;my_field_1&apos;&lt;/span&gt; : &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;blah&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
}

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I find that I get a segfault. GDB tracks it back to line 99 of t_scope.h, where it looks like we try to get a t_field object from the parent struct by name, and then ultimately don&apos;t check if we actually got back something valid or not. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
